The paper heavily relies on logic and graph theory to analyze timed systems with data structures. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel proof technique for the analysis of timed systems enriched with auxiliary data structures, which suggests that it could also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also deals with formal languages and automata, which could place it in the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses a highly non-trivial argument to show the logical definability of graph properties, which could make it relevant to the Logic and Verification (cs.LG) sub-category.
